text:
The Oni is wielding a samurai weapon called a Tetsubo. A Tetsubo is a 4ft long, 2 inches around piece of white oak wrapped in black leather with iron studs. The grip is designed for 2-handed use but larger samurai could wield it one-handed. Unlike a baseball bat they rarely break and are designed for rupturing organs and shattering bones. An unprotect arm for example could be broken off if the samurai has sufficient strength. A strike to the chest could arteries to explode internally, rupture lungs or the heart with enough strength. 
Generally the weapon is considered to be dishonorable and would only be used a last resort or for to punish law breakers. Samurai of a more evil or unruly nature would use them anyways.
Oni are depicted as using them in the lore to generate more terror and panic amongst their enemies.

Typically a baseball bat will break before it can cause that kind of and is of course designed to launch small round objects. So Tetsubo not a bat.
